Interface NamingStrategy

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultNamingStrategy

    public interface NamingStrategy
    An interface, allowing the adjustment of the edm-to-java name mapping.

    • Method Detail

      • getNameFromEntity

        String getNameFromEntity(String entityName,
                         String entityLabel)
        Converts the given name and label of an edm entity into a java name.

        This method can be used to remove unwanted pre-/suffixes or map the name completely new.

        The actual creation of java-style names (class, variable, constants etc.) is done later, based on the name returned by this method.

        For best results, the name returned should be given in CamelCase.

        Parameters:
        entityName - The entity name, taken from the metadata file.
        entityLabel - The entity label, taken from the metadata file.
        Returns:
        The name to be used in the generated java files.

      • getNameFromProperty

        String getNameFromProperty(String propertyName,
                           String propertyLabel)
        Converts the given name and label of an edm property into a java name.

        This method can be used to remove unwanted pre-/suffixes or map the name completely new.

        The actual creation of java-style names (class, variable, constants etc.) is done later, based on the name returned by this method.

        For best results, the name returned should be given in CamelCase.

        Parameters:
        propertyName - The property name, taken from the metadata files.
        propertyLabel - The property label, taken from the metadata file.
        Returns:
        The name to be used in the generated java files.
